{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Bug}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Shelmet}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Bug|prevnum=615|prev=Cryogonal|nextnum=617|next=Accelgor|roundleft=bl|roundright=br}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Shelmet\n|jname=チョボマキ\n|tmname=Chobomaki\n|category=Snail\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Bug\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Hydration\n|ability2=Shell Armor\n|abilityd=Overcoat\n|ndex=616\n|udex=122\n|u2dex=157\n|karea=Mountain\n|kdex=024\n|height-ftin=1\'04"\n|height-m=0.4\n|weight-lbs=17.0\n|weight-kg=7.7\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Bug\n|eggcycles=15\n|expyield=61\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|gendercode=127\n|color=Red\n|catchrate=200\n|evtotal=1\n|evde=1\n|body=01\n|pokefordex=shelmet\n|generation=5\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Shelmet\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'チョボマキ\'\'\' \'\'Chobomaki\'\') is a {{type|Bug}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation V]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] into {{p|Accelgor}} when [[trade]]d for a {{p|Karrablast}}, which evolves into {{p|Escavalier}} simultaneously. Neither evolves if at least one holds an [[Everstone]] during the trade.\n\n==Biology==\nShelmet is a bivalve or snail-like Pokémon. Its gray shell resembles a knight\'s visor, with a coiling spiral of its shell further back. The shell has protrusions on the underside, which it apparently uses as legs. Its inner body is pink with a long, puckered mouth, and green markings below its eyes. It closes the lid on its helmet-like shell as a defensive tactic, and can spit a poisonous sticky fluid. It thrives in moist habitats like bogs and swamps.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Bianca Shelmet.png|thumb|left|250px|Shelmet in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\nShelmet debuted in \'\'[[BW049|Enter Elesa, Electrifying Gym Leader!]]\'\', under the ownership of {{an|Bianca}}. She used it in her [[Gym]] {{pkmn|battle}} with [[Elesa]]. However, it was quickly defeated by Elesa\'s {{p|Zebstrika}}. It reappeared in \'\'[[BW063|Evolution Exchange Excitement!]]\'\', where it was [[trade]]d with [[Professor Juniper]] for her {{p|Karrablast}}, causing it to [[Evolution|evolve]].\n\n===Minor appearances===\nA Shelmet appeared in a fantasy in \'\'[[BW062|Crisis at Chargestone Cave!]]\'\'.\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Unova}}\n{{Animedexbody|BW049|Shelmet|Ash\'s Pokédex|Shelmet, the Snail Pokémon. Shelmet can spit a sticky poisonous acid when attacking, and it can defend itself by closing its shell.}}\n{{Animedexbody|BW063|Shelmet|Ash\'s Pokédex|Shelmet, the Snail Pokémon. Shelmet closes its shell to protect itself from attacks. It also produces and spits out a poisonous, sticky liquid.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Best Wishes\'\'|Unova}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Whitley Shelmet Adventures.png|thumb|200px|Shelmet in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Be the Best! Pokémon B+W manga===\nA Shelmet appeared in \'\'[[PBW4|Challenge the Battle Subway!]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nShelmet debuted in \'\'[[PS479|The Case of the Missing Pokémon]]\'\', where it was one of the Pokémon kidnapped by [[Team Plasma]]. It was later returned to its {{pkmn|Trainer}} after being found in a stronghold.\n\n{{tc|Baker}} Chris owns a Shelmet. It first appeared in \'\'[[PS486|Unraveling Mysteries]]\'\'.\n\nA Shelmet liberated by Team Plasma appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[PS529|Pokédex Lecture]]\'\'.\n\nA Shelmet was {{pkmn2|caught}} by {{adv|Whitley}} in [[PS543]]. In the same chapter, it was [[trade]]d to {{adv|Blake}} for his {{p|Karrablast}}, subsequently evolved into Accelgor, and then traded back.\n\nA Shelmet appeared in \'\'[[PAXY30|Pinsir Changes]]\'\'.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Shelmet (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Bug}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=V}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=V|reg1=Unova|num1=122|label1={{gameabbrev5|BW}}:|reg2=Unova|num2=157|label2={{gameabbrev5|B2W2}}:}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Black|t=FFF|entry=Wh