met-->\n|evocandy=50\n|stamina=137\n|attack=72\n|defense=140\n|fast={{m|Acid}}, {{m|Infestation}}\n|special={{m|Bug Buzz}}, {{m|Body Slam}}, {{m|Signal Beam}}\n}}\n|}\n\n===Evolution===\n{{evobox-2\n|type1=Bug\n|no1=616\n|name1=Shelmet\n|type1-1=Bug\n|evo1={{bag|Pal Pad}}{{MS|588}}<br>{{color2|000|Trade}}<br><small>for {{pcolor|Karrablast|000}}\n|no2=617\n|name2=Accelgor\n|type1-2=Bug\n}}\n\n===Sprites===\n{{Spritebox/Header|type=Bug}}\n{{Spritebox/NA|gen=V}}\n{{Spritebox/5|ndex=616}}\n{{Spritebox/6|ndex=616}}\n{{Spritebox/7|ndex=616}}\n{{Spritebox/Footer|616|Shelmet}}\n\n==Trivia==\n* Shelmet and {{p|Karrablast}} are the only Pokémon that have to be traded with a specific Pokémon to evolve, having to be traded with each other.\n* Although {{p|Escavalier}} gains a secondary {{t|Steel}} type from its armor, Shelmet is a pure {{type|Bug}} despite wearing the same armor.\n\n===Origin===\nShelmet appears to be based on a combination of a {{wp|snail}}, possibly a {{wp|scaly-foot snail}}, whose shell\'s outer layer is made of iron compounds; and a {{wp|close helmet}}. It also may also be based on a {{wp|nautilus}}.\n\nKarrablast and Shelmet may be a reference to {{wp|coevolution}}, where the evolution of one species is influenced by changes in another species; in this case, the relationship between predator and prey.\n\n====Name origin====\nShelmet is a combination of \'\'shell\'\' and \'\'helmet\'\'.\n\nChobomaki may be a combination of おちょぼ口 \'\'ochoboguchi\'\' (puckered-up mouth) and 巻き \'\'maki\'\' (to coil or roll).\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Bug|type2=Bug\n|ja=チョボマキ \'\'Chobomaki\'\'|jameaning=From {{tt|おちょぼ口 \'\'ochoboguchi\'\'|puckered-up mouth}} and {{tt|巻き \'\'maki\'\'|to coil, to roll}}\n|fr=Escargaume|frmeaning=From \'\'{{tt|escargot|snail}}\'\' and \'\'{{tt|heaume|helmet}}\'\'\n|es=Shelmet|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Schnuthelm|demeaning=From \'\'{{tt|Schnute|pouting mouth}}\'\' and \'\'{{tt|Helm|helmet}}\'\'\n|it=Shelmet|itmean